GitHub’s current docs prefer Bearer over token. Some org policies now reject token. It’s a safe swap:

s.headers.update({
    "Authorization": f"Bearer {token}",
    ...
})

JSON decode resilience
Occasionally the API may transiently return HTML (proxies). One quick retry on JSON decode helps:

try:
    data = response.json() or []
except ValueError:
    print("[WARN] Non-JSON response; retrying once after short sleep…")
    time.sleep(2)
    try:
        data = response.json() or []
    except ValueError:
        print("[ERROR] Non-JSON response from GitHub; aborting.")
        break
